Project Introduction¶

Using 437 recruitment information captured by Lagou.com, I analyze Shenzhen data analysis positions from multiple dimensions and understand the current status of the data analyst industry.

Keywords¶

  • Data exploration and analysis, matplotlib visualization, stuttering word segmentation, word cloud diagram

data_cleaned = data.dropna()
# Processing the salary column: Assume that the salary is an interval, the format is "XXk-YYk"
# First split the salary column, extract the minimum and maximum salary and convert them to numeric type
data_cleaned['salary_min'] = data_cleaned['salary'].str.extract(r'(\d+)k')[0].astype(int) * 1000
data_cleaned['salary_max'] = data_cleaned['salary'].str.extract(r'-(\d+)k')[0].astype(int) * 1000

# You can calculate the average salary, that is, the expected salary
data_cleaned['salary_avg'] = (data_cleaned['salary_min'] + data_cleaned['salary_max']) / 2

# Use Box Plot performs basic statistical analysis on salary
plt.figure(figsize=(10, 6))
sns.boxplot(x=data_cleaned['salary_avg'])
plt.title('Salary Distribution (Boxplot)')
plt.xlabel('Average Salary (in CNY)')
plt.show()

As of 2024, the minimum wage standards in Shenzhen are as follows: Full-time employees: The minimum monthly wage is RMB 2,360. Part-time employees: The minimum hourly wage is RMB 22.2. Source: https://www.ceicdata.com/en/china/standard-of-monthly-minimum-wage/standard-of-monthly-minimum-wage-guangdong-shenzhen

3. Data Exploration and Analysis¶

Analyze from multiple dimensions (region, salary, years of work, education, industry, company size, job requirements), and analyze the regional distribution of data analysts, salary distribution, and the correlation between various fields.

3.1. Demand for data analyst positions in different regions¶

In [23]:

Summary: It is not difficult to see that the demand in Nanshan District is far ahead of other districts. It is worthy of being the gathering place of Shenzhen Internet (for example, Tencent, ZTE, etc.). Of course, Futian and Baoan also have relatively large demand, while other districts have very few or even some new districts have no demand. This shows that data analyst is indeed a sunrise industry, so it is preferred to apply for jobs in Nanshan, Futian and Baoan.

3.5. Salary range distribution of data analysts¶

In [27]:
# Remove 'k' or 'K' characters from the salary field
clean_salary = [re.sub('[k|K]', '', i) for i in data.salary]

# Convert the salary data to DataFrame format
salary = pd.DataFrame(clean_salary, columns=['salary'])
salary_s = pd.DataFrame((x.split('-') for x in salary['salary']), columns=['bottomSalary', 'topSalary'])

# Change the field format
salary_s['bottomSalary'] = salary_s['bottomSalary'].astype(np.int)
salary_s['topSalary'] = salary_s['topSalary'].astype(np.int)

# Calculate the average value
salary_avg = [(salary_s['bottomSalary'][i] + salary_s['topSalary'][i]) / 2 for i in range(len(salary_s))]
salary_s['avgSalary'] = salary_avg

# Concatenate the salary_s table with the original table
data = pd.merge(data, salary_s, right_index=True, left_index=True)

import pandas as pd

# Assume your salary column is stored in the form of "7k-10k"
# Split the 'salary' column into 'salary_min' and 'salary_max'
data_final_with_dummies[['salary_min', 'salary_max']] = data_final_with_dummies['salary'].str.extract(r'(\d+)k-(\d+)k')

# Convert 'salary_min' and 'salary_max' to numeric type and multiply by 1000
data_final_with_dummies['salary_min'] = data_final_with_dummies['salary_min'].astype(float) * 1000
data_final_with_dummies['salary_max'] = data_final_with_dummies['salary_max'].astype(float) * 1000

# Calculate the average salary and store it in decimal form
data_final_with_dummies['salary_avg'] = (data_final_with_dummies['salary_min'] + data_final_with_dummies['salary_max']) / 2

# View the converted result
print(data_final_with_dummies[['salary', 'salary_avg']].head())

Through the above analysis, we can draw the following conclusions:

a. In Shenzhen, the demand for data analyst positions is mainly concentrated in Nanshan and Futian, that is, the Internet gathering place, with a high overall salary (basically above 8K), the academic requirements are not particularly high (above undergraduate), the demand for large companies is large, and a large number of work experience requirements are concentrated in 1-3 years.

b. The industry field distributed by data analysts is mainly the mobile Internet industry, but it has also begun to penetrate into traditional industries (such as finance and education).

c. The most frequently possessed skills of data analysts are: SQL, Python, mathematical statistics, data sensitivity, Excel, SAS, SPSS, Hadoop, machine learning, etc., among which mathematical statistics, SQL, Python, and Excel are essential skills.

d. Machine learning and big data mining are the right direction to move towards high salaries.
